HEADWORD: Isogonism
<hw>I*sog"o*nism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets>
+ Gr. <?/ offspring, generative parts.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The quality of having similar sexual zooids or gonophores and
dissimilar hydrants; -- said of certain hydroids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

